
[1]pistol

   PIS'TOL, n. A small fire-arm, or the smallest fire-arm used, differing
   from a musket chiefly in size. Pistols are of different lengths, and
   borne by horsemen in cases at the saddle bow, or by a girdle. Small
   pistols are carried in the pocket.

   PIS'TOL, v.t. To shoot with a pistol.
